**ICONIK Ad Hooks Library:**

​​**PART 1: THE AD CREATION SYSTEM**

**FRAMEWORK: THE 3-LAYER CREATIVE STACK**

Think of every ad as having 3 components that can be independently
tested:

HOOK (First 3 seconds) →BODY (Proof mechanism) →CTA (Offer clarity)

Your job is to **systematize each layer** so you\'re not starting from
scratch every time.

**LAYER 1: HOOK BANK (12 Core Templates)**

Stop improvising hooks. Build a **reusable hook library** based on
proven psychological triggers. Here are your 12:

  ------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Hook Type**                   **Template**                                                                                              **Example for Iconik**
                                                                                                                                            
  **1. Contrarian Advice**        \"They told you \[common advice\], but that\'s terrible if you \[pain point\]\"                           \"They told you to tuck in your shirt to look polished---but that\'s terrible advice if you have a tummy.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **2. Pattern Interrupt**        \"Stop \[doing X\]. Here\'s what \[authority figure\] does instead.\"                                     \"Stop wearing A-line kurtas to hide your waist. Here\'s what stylists do for apple-shaped women.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **3. Transformation Tease**     \"\[Name\] used to \[pain\]. Now she \[dream outcome\]. Here\'s how.\"                                    \"Priya used to avoid fitted clothes. Now she wears structured blazers to client meetings. Here\'s the science.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **4. Pain Amplification**       \"You\'ve tried \[solution 1\], \[solution 2\], \[solution 3\]. You still feel \[pain\]. Here\'s why.\"   \"High-waisted jeans? They roll down. Belted dresses? They highlight your tummy. You still feel bulky. Here\'s why.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **5. Authority Credibility**    \"After styling \[X\] women with \[pain\], I\'ve learned \[insight\].\"                                   \"After styling 300+ apple-shaped women, I\'ve learned empire cuts do more harm than good.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **6. Myth-Busting**             \"The fashion industry lied to you about \[X\]. Here\'s the truth.\"                                      \"The fashion industry lied about \'dressing for your body type.\' Here\'s what actually works.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **7. Urgency Framing**          \"If you\'re \[age/life stage\], you have \[timeframe\] to fix this before \[consequence\].\"             \"If you\'re 35+, you have 5 years before your wardrobe makes you invisible at work.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **8. Social Proof Opener**      \"\[X\]% of women with \[pain\] make this mistake. Are you one of them?\"                                 \"87% of women with heavy arms wear sleeveless to \'feel confident.\' It backfires. Here\'s why.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **9. Before/After Contrast**    \"\[Visual\]. Left = \[pain\]. Right = \[solution\]. The difference? \[insight\].\"                       \"Left: Flowy kurta. Right: Structured kurta. The difference? Vertical seams.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **10. Problem Stacking**        \"You have \[pain 1\]. And \[pain 2\]. And \[pain 3\]. They\'re all connected.\"                          \"You have a tummy. And short height. And modest dressing rules. They\'re all solvable with one system.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **11. Insider Secret**          \"Stylists don\'t tell you this, but \[insight\].\"                                                       \"Stylists don\'t tell you this, but 80% of \'flattering\' advice is for Western body types.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  **12. Aspirational Identity**   \"Women who \[dream outcome\] don\'t \[common behavior\]. They \[new behavior\].\"                        \"Women who command respect in meetings don\'t wear flowy tops. They wear structured silhouettes.\"
                                                                                                                                            
  ------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Your Action:** Pick 3-4 hook types per week. Rotate them. Track which
ones yield the lowest CPM/highest CTR.

**LAYER 2: BODY STRUCTURE (3 Proven Formulas)**

Once the hook stops the scroll, the **body** must justify the click. Use
these 3 frameworks:

**Formula A: Problem →Agitation →Science →Proof**

1\. \"Let\'s be honest: \[common pain\].\"

2\. \"You\'ve tried \[failed solution 1\], \[failed solution 2\]. You
still feel \[emotion\].\"

3\. \"Here\'s the science: \[insight about body type/color/fabric\].\"

4\. \"We styled \[name\]---her pain\]. We gave her \[solution\]. She
\[result\].\"

**Formula B: Authority →Insight →Case Study**

1\. \"After styling \[X\] women with \[pain\], I\'ve learned
\[counterintuitive insight\].\"

2\. \"The mistake? \[common behavior\].\"

3\. \"The fix? \[specific solution\].\"

4\. \"\[Name\] from \[city\]---her pain\]. Now she \[result\].\"

**Formula C: Myth-Busting →Reframe →Proof**

1\. \"The fashion industry says \[myth\].\"

2\. \"But if you\'re \[body type/age/lifestyle\], that\'s wrong. Here\'s
why: \[science\].\"

3\. \"We proved it with \[name\]. \[Her transformation\].\"

**Your Action:** Every ad must follow one of these 3 formulas. No
exceptions.

**LAYER 3: CTA ARCHITECTURE (Offer Clarity + Scarcity)**

Your CTA has 3 jobs:

1.  **Clarify the offer** (What they get for ₹999).

2.  **Remove friction** (Why it\'s risk-free).

3.  **Create urgency** (Why they must act now).

**Template:**

\"₹999. \[What they get\]. \[Scarcity trigger\]. \[Link/CTA\].\"

**Examples:**

-   \"₹999. Your personalized Blueprint + 1-hour styling call. 8 slots
    left this week. Link below.\"

-   \"₹999. 16 looks tailored to your body type and lifestyle. Next
    batch starts Monday. Book now.\"

**PART 2: THE TESTING SYSTEM**

**THE 3x3x3 TESTING MATRIX**

You can\'t test everything at once. Use this hierarchy:

PHASE 1: Hook Testing (Week 1-2)

→Test 3 hooks with the same body + CTA.

→Winner = lowest CPM + highest CTR (\>2%).

PHASE 2: Body Testing (Week 3-4)

→Test 3 body formulas with the winning hook.

→Winner = highest landing page CTR.

PHASE 3: Offer Testing (Week 5-6)

→Test 3 CTA variations with the winning hook + body.

→Winner = lowest CAC + highest conversion rate.

**Example Week 1:**

-   Ad 1: Contrarian Hook + Formula A + Standard CTA

-   Ad 2: Pain Amplification Hook + Formula A + Standard CTA

-   Ad 3: Transformation Hook + Formula A + Standard CTA

**Budget Allocation:** ₹00/day per ad for 3 days. Kill losers on Day 4.
Scale winner to ₹000/day.

**THE TRACKER (Google Sheet Template)**

  ----------- --------------- ------------------ ---------- ----------- ----------------- --------- --------- --------------- ----------------- --------- ---------- ------------
  **Ad ID**   **Hook Type**   **Body Formula**   **CTA**    **Spend**   **Impressions**   **CPM**   **CTR**   **LP Clicks**   **Conversions**   **CAC**   **ROAS**   **Status**
                                                                                                                                                                     
  A1          Contrarian      Formula A          Scarcity   ₹500        45K               ₹3        2.8%      1260            3                 ₹00       4.0x       SCALE
                                                                                                                                                                     
  A2          Pain Amp        Formula A          Scarcity   ₹500        47K               ₹2        2.1%      987             2                 ₹50       2.7x       KILL
                                                                                                                                                                     
  ----------- --------------- ------------------ ---------- ----------- ----------------- --------- --------- --------------- ----------------- --------- ---------- ------------

**Rules:**

-   CTR \< 2% after 3 days? Kill it.

-   CAC \> ₹00 after 5 days? Kill it.

-   ROAS \> 3x after 7 days? Scale to ₹000/day.

